Germany's basketball star, Dirk Nowitzki, played his final home game in the NBA on Tuesday night, announcing the end of an illustrious career in front of a sellout crowd. Nowitzki played a record 21 seasons with the Dallas Mavericks and is set to end his career in San Antonio on Wednesday night, in the last game of the Maverick's season. The German 14-time All-StarÂ scored 30 points in his final home game, a Dallas victory over the Phoenix Suns 120-109. More to come...